The records of this genus are from Japan to Queensland, Australia (Fig. 2) and the island systems of the western Pacific Ocean, with the deepest record of 657 m in the Flores Sea (
Nakamura and Child 1990
; 
Bamber 1992
; 

Mueller
1993

). The new species was obtained from 1317.5 m, increasing the depth range of this genus. The occurrence of the new species fills a gap in the distribution 
'corridor'
of this genus, connecting the species in Japan with the Philippines and equatorial and Australian species.
